Here's a PlantUML sequence diagram representing the control flow for a typical Express.js application based on the repository summary:

```plantuml
@startuml quasirsg_Henry-M3

actor Client
participant "Express Server" as Server
participant "Middleware" as Middleware
participant "Router" as Router
participant "Controller" as Controller
participant "Model" as Model
database "Database" as DB

Client -> Server: HTTP Request
activate Server

Server -> Middleware: Pass request
activate Middleware
Middleware -> Middleware: Process request (e.g., body parsing, authentication)
Middleware --> Server: Modified request
deactivate Middleware

Server -> Router: Route request
activate Router
Router -> Controller: Delegate to appropriate controller
deactivate Router

activate Controller
Controller -> Model: Request data
activate Model
Model -> DB: Query database
DB --> Model: Return data
Model --> Controller: Return processed data
deactivate Model

Controller -> Controller: Process data
Controller --> Server: Send response
deactivate Controller

Server --> Client: HTTP Response
deactivate Server

@enduml
```